column5: Where? I just paid 130.2 at Esso on Greenhill and King.

I read the title of this and it brought me a flash back a few of us might remember from the early 80's - a strange phenomenon called gas wars? At the peak I was driving a cab in London Ont, and one day they had a photo - a tanker truck had pulled into the Petro Canada around the corner from the flop house I shared with 5 other poor starving students (or used-to-be-students). He was pumping INTO the tanker because they were selling it for $0.10 / litre....
